Shows the BitLocker status for disks

manage-bde -status


Shows the BitLocker protectors/protection keys for drive C

manage-bde -protectors -get C


PowerShell version for checking BitLocker

Get-BitLockerVolume


Suspending BitLocker before firmware/BIOS changes

Suspend-BitLocker -MountPoint "C:" -RebootCount 1 Resume-BitLocker -MountPoint "C:"


Add the TPM Key Protector

Add-BitLockerKeyProtector -MountPoint "C:" -TpmProtector


Back up a Recovery Key

Add-BitLockerKeyProtector -MountPoint "C:" -RecoveryPasswordProtector


Turn Protection On

Resume-BitLocker -MountPoint "C:"


Verify the Fix

Get-BitLockerVolume -MountPoint C:


Undo "Turn Protection On

Suspend-BitLocker -MountPoint "C:" -RebootCount 0


Undo the Key Protectors

Get-BitLockerVolume -MountPoint "C:" | Select-Object -ExpandProperty KeyProtector


To delete all key protectors associated with the drive at once


$Volume = Get-BitLockerVolume -MountPoint "C:"
foreach ($Protector in $Volume.KeyProtector) {
    Remove-BitLockerKeyProtector -MountPoint "C:" -KeyProtectorId $Protector.KeyProtectorId
}











